{{page-title "Career Caddy Sender — Privacy Policy"}}
<div class="container mx-auto max-w-3xl py-6 px-4 space-y-6">

  <Panel::Card>
    <h1 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800 mb-2">
      Career Caddy Sender — Privacy Policy
    </h1>
    <p class="text-gray-500 text-sm">
      This page describes what data the Career Caddy Sender browser extension
      collects, when, and why. It is the privacy policy referenced from the
      Chrome Web Store and Firefox Add-ons listings.
    </p>
  </Panel::Card>

  <Panel::Card>
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-3">Summary</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-600">
      The extension only talks to one server: your Career Caddy account at
      <code class="text-sm">careercaddy.online</code>. It never sends data to
      third parties, never uses tracking pixels, and never reads page content
      unless you click its toolbar button. Everything the extension does is
      triggered by an explicit click — there is no background scanning of the
      pages you visit.
    </p>
  </Panel::Card>

  <Panel::Card>
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-3">
      Data we collect — and when
    </h2>

    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-800 mt-4 mb-2">
      When you click the toolbar icon to open the popup
    </h3>
    <p class="text-gray-600 mb-3">
      The extension reads
      <strong>only the URL of the active tab</strong>
      and asks your Career Caddy library whether that URL is already tracked.
      This single request returns either "yes, here it is" with a link, or "no"
      — at which point the popup shows the Send button. No page content is read
      for this lookup. The request is triggered by your click on the toolbar
      action; there is no polling, no tab change listener, and no background
      scan of any kind.
    </p>

    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-800 mt-4 mb-2">
      When you click "Send this page"
    </h3>
    <p class="text-gray-600 mb-3">
      The extension reads the URL of the active tab and the page's text
      (specifically
      <code class="text-sm">document.body.innerText</code>), and POSTs both to
      your Career Caddy account. The text is parsed into a
      <strong>JobPost</strong>
      record owned by your account.
    </p>

    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-800 mt-4 mb-2">
      When you click "Connect"
    </h3>
    <p class="text-gray-600">
      You enter your Career Caddy username and password. These are transmitted
      to your account only to mint a dedicated, revocable API key. Your password
      is
      <strong>never stored</strong>
      by the extension. The temporary access token returned by the login step is
      discarded immediately after the API key is created. Only the API key
      persists.
    </p>
  </Panel::Card>

  <Panel::Card>
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-3">
      What is stored locally
    </h2>
    <p class="text-gray-600 mb-3">
      The extension uses your browser's
      <code class="text-sm">storage.local</code>
      for the following items, all scoped to the extension itself:
    </p>
    <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-600 list-disc list-inside">
      <li>The
        <strong>API key</strong>
        and key id — used to authenticate requests to your Career Caddy account.
        Revocable from
        <em>Settings → API Keys</em>
        in Career Caddy, or by clicking
        <em>Disconnect</em>
        in the extension popup.</li>
      <li>Your
        <strong>username</strong>
        — shown in the popup footer so you know which account is connected.</li>
      <li>Your
        <strong>theme and palette preferences</strong>
        — so the popup matches the way you've configured Career Caddy.</li>
      <li>Your
        <strong>"Auto-score against career data"</strong>
        preference — so the toggle remembers its state.</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="text-gray-600 mt-3">
      Nothing in this list is transmitted to third parties.
    </p>
  </Panel::Card>

  <Panel::Card>
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-3">
      What we do NOT do
    </h2>
    <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-600 list-disc list-inside">
      <li>We do not read page content unless you click the Send button.</li>
      <li>We do not scan the URLs of tabs you have not opened the popup on.</li>
      <li>We do not track which sites you visit.</li>
      <li>We do not sell or share data with anyone.</li>
      <li>We do not use the data we receive for any purpose other than creating
        and managing the JobPost records you have asked us to keep.</li>
      <li>We do not include analytics, telemetry, or third-party scripts in the
        extension.</li>
    </ul>
  </Panel::Card>

  <Panel::Card>
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-3">Permissions</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-600 mb-3">
      The extension requests these permissions, and only uses them for the
      purposes described:
    </p>
    <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-600 list-disc list-inside">
      <li><strong>activeTab</strong>
        and
        <strong>scripting</strong>
        — read the active tab's URL when you open the popup, and the page's text
        when you click Send.</li>
      <li><strong>storage</strong>
        — persist the API key, username, and preferences described above.</li>
      <li><strong>notifications</strong>
        — show an OS notification when a Send completes (so you know the page
        was added).</li>
      <li><strong>alarms</strong>
        — the background poll cadence used to wait for the parse and score
        results before firing a notification.</li>
      <li><strong>host_permissions: &lt;all_urls&gt;</strong>
        — required for active-tab text capture to work on arbitrary careers,
        ATS, and job-board domains. All
        <em>network requests</em>
        go to a single hardcoded origin (<code
          class="text-sm"
        >https://api.careercaddy.online</code>);
        <code class="text-sm">&lt;all_urls&gt;</code>
        is for reads, not network egress.</li>
    </ul>
  </Panel::Card>

  <Panel::Card>
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-3">
      Retention and deletion
    </h2>
    <p class="text-gray-600">
      Anything submitted via the extension lives in your Career Caddy account
      just like data you create through the website. Retention and deletion
      follow the same rules as the rest of your account — delete a JobPost from
      Career Caddy and it is gone. Delete your account and all associated data
      is removed.
    </p>
  </Panel::Card>

  <Panel::Card>
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-3">Revocation</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-600">
      To stop the extension from accessing your account at any time, either
      click
      <em>Disconnect</em>
      in the extension popup, or revoke the named key under
      <em>Settings → API Keys</em>
      in Career Caddy. Either action immediately invalidates the extension's
      access; the next request will be rejected and the extension will prompt
      you to reconnect.
    </p>
  </Panel::Card>

  <Panel::Card>
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-3">Contact</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-600">
      Questions about this policy or the extension's behavior? Email
      <a
        class="text-accent-700 underline"
        href="mailto:webmaster@careercaddy.online"
      >webmaster@careercaddy.online</a>.
    </p>
  </Panel::Card>

</div>